<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-08-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-08-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="34" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d34">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 4885/7.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Monroe</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">La
                                    Paz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-08-05"><hi rend="italic">August 5,
                                1908</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 389.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that during
                            Friday night, July 24, 1908, Dr. Fernando E. Guachalla, President-elect
                            of Bolivia, died. The Government flags were at half-staff for three
                            days, as was the flag of this legation. Dr. Claudio Pinilla, minister
                            for foreign affairs of Bolivia, asks me to thank my Government for the
                            sympathy expressed in its name on the occasion of the death of Dr.
                            Guachalla.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">G. L. Monroe,</hi>
                            Jr.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>